description.narrative: In 2020, with support from the Country Office, 2,996 young people aged 10-24 (48% girls) participated in at least one skill development programme offered as part of life skills or vocational programmes. The Country Office also contributed to the empowerment of 223 vulnerable adolescents and youths (111 girls and young women) through civic service training. It also promoted young people’s engagement and participation in building social cohesion and preventing the spread of COVID-19. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:28/01/2021
